In java if we use '==' operator with primitves then it will perform value comparison. 
And if we use '==' operator with non-primitives then it will perform ref. comparison.
So, to prove that all the ref. in above example pointing to the same object we can write.
S.O.P(r1 == r2);
S.O.P(r1 == r3);

Another method to perform the ref. comparison is through Hash code-
This method is of Object Class(hashCode method)
S.O.P(r1.hashCode);//printing the hashCode(unique ID) of object that r1 points to
S.O.P(r2.hashCode);//printing the hashCode(unique ID) of object that r2 points to
If both hashCode are same then both the ref. var points to the same object otherwise not.

